# One pkgsrc package origin (category/name) per line. These are packages the
# other Cross-Platform Action ports get from the official pkgsrc binary
# mirrors but that have no prebuilt vax builds.
#
# These are cross-compiled on a NetBSD/amd64 host (USE_CROSS_COMPILE=yes), not
# built on emulated vax. Cross-compiling builds the whole build-tool closure
# (perl, texinfo, bison) NATIVELY as tool-dependencies and never cross-builds a
# target perl, so the openssl/perl chain that was infeasible on the emulated
# VAX is no longer a blocker. curl (needs openssl -> perl) is a candidate to
# add now that cross-compiling removes that blocker.
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
shells/bash
net/rsync

# sudo's configure runs a SECOND compiler probe (AX_PROG_CC_FOR_BUILD) for a
# native BUILD compiler; left alone it falls back to the pkgsrc wrapper `gcc`
# (which points at the vax cross-compiler) and fails ("cannot run C compiled
# programs"). Fixed in cross-build.sh by feeding it pkgsrc's ${NATIVE_CC}
# (/usr/bin/cc -B /usr/libexec -B /usr/bin) via CONFIGURE_ENV -- the -B flags
# force the native as/ld. Cross-builds cleanly.
security/sudo

# curl: was excluded on the emulated VAX (needs openssl -> perl). Cross-compiling
# builds perl/build-tools natively as tool-deps, and curl links the base
# OpenSSL + zlib already in the vax sysroot (from build.sh distribution), so no
# target openssl/zlib build is needed at all. Cross-builds green with no fixes;
# vax runtime deps pulled: libidn2, libunistring, libxml2, nghttp2, xmlcatmgr.
www/curl
